"7016A068100G V-1.00" is silkscreened on the main board in the FCC photos. :"7016A071200E V1.00" is silkscreened on the 11ac wireless module.
This device would seem to very similar (if not identical to) the [[ZyXEL NBG6716]].
Default settings (as well as the FC:F5:28 OUI) are per the FCC sample label. :The label indicates the default SSID formats are '''VIDEOTRON'''XXXX and :'''VIDEOTRON'''XXXX-5GHz (presumed upper-case hex digits for '''XXXX''').
{{Used by service|Vid√©otron}}, a Canadian ISP, is assumed to be one of the primary users of this device. :However, appearances on eBay would indicate generic versions of were distributed.
Default SSID and the 90:EF:68 OUI used in this entry are per marketplace labels.
===Probable used PSU(s)=== The power adapter shown in the FCC photos is a '''DVE''' DSA-24PFD-15 FUS 120200.
